title: Literary landmarks of Edinburgh,
author: Hutton, Laurence
snippet: West Register Street by the narrow alley running now between the New Register House and the new Cafe Royal. This little paved foot-path was, in the time of Ambrose's, a green lane called Gabriel's Road, leading diagonally across the New Town to Silvermills, and it is said still to claim its ancient privilege of a right of way.

title: Story of a Stolen Heir. A novel
author: Bertram, James Glass.
snippet: A night or two after the execution of HughBrogan, Mr Joseph Liddell was on his wayto the Cafe Royal, to enjoy his usualtumbler of toddy. Since he had become apartner in the great firm, he had forsakenhis little comfortable snuggery in the LowCalton, and taken evening refreshment inthe more aristocratic tavern of RegisterStreet.
